@startuml
title Sequence Diagram - Level 2
title US 2.2.2 - Create, Update, and Search Vessels

participant "REST Client" as Client
participant "Backend API" as API
database "Database" as DB

== Create Vessel ==

Client -> API : POST /api/vessel\nBody: { imoNumber, name, vesselTypeId, operator }
API -> DB : INSERT INTO Vessels (...)
DB --> API : New Vessel (ImoNumber)
API --> Client : 201 Created\nBody: { imoNumber, name, vesselTypeId, operator }

== Update Vessel ==

Client -> API : PUT /api/vessel/{imo}\nBody: { updated fields }
API -> DB : UPDATE Vessels SET ... WHERE ImoNumber = {imo}
DB --> API : Success
API --> Client : 200 OK\nBody: { imoNumber, name, vesselTypeId, operator }

== Search and Filter Vessels ==

Client -> API : GET /api/vessel/search?imo={imo?}&name={name?}&operatorName={operator?}
API -> DB : SELECT * FROM Vessels\nWHERE (ImoNumber = 'imo' OR 'imo' IS NULL)\nAND (LOWER(Name) LIKE '%name%' OR 'name' IS NULL)\nAND (LOWER(Operator) LIKE '%operator%' OR 'operator' IS NULL)
DB --> API : List of matching Vessels
API --> Client : 200 OK\nBody: [ { imoNumber, name, vesselTypeId, operator }, ... ]

@enduml

